The paper presents a method for a new classification task using deep reinforcement learning, which involves processing hierarchical input and making decisions with a cost constraint. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.AI (artificial intelligence) for the use of reinforcement learning, cs.LG (machine learning) for the classification task, cs.CL (computation and language) for the natural language processing aspect, cs.CR (cryptography and security) for the malware detection application, and cs.DB (databases) for the hierarchical data representation.
